      "text": " Let  $h$  be the divisor corresponding to a line bundle  $\\mathcal{L}$  on  $X$ . We denote the pullback of  $h$  under the *i*-th projection as  $h_i$ . The morphism  $\\rho$  is an involution map, so  $\\rho_*\\eta^*h_1 = \\rho_*\\eta^*h_2$ . We define  $H = \\rho_*\\eta^*h_1 = \\rho_*\\eta^*h_2$  and  $\\delta = \\frac{1}{2}\\rho_*E$ . The following proposition may be known to experts but I could not find appropriate references, so I will provide a proof.",
