      "text": " *Proof.* Let  $\\pi : \\mathbb{P}(E_{\\mathcal{L}}) \\to X^{[2]}$  be the projection map of a projective bundle. Consider the normal sheaf  $\\mathcal{N} := \\mathcal{N}_{Z_2/X \\times X^{[2]}}$  and the closed immersion  $j: Z_2 \\to X \\times X^{[2]}$  with the composition  $q: Z_2 \\to X$  of  $\\eta$  and the first projection. The morphism  $\\pi_1|_{Z_2}: Z_2 \\to X^{[2]}$  is a finite flat morphism, and  $\\pi_{2*}(\\pi_1^*\\mathcal{L}\\otimes\\mathcal{O}_{Z_2})$  is a locally free sheaf on  $X^{[2]}$ , so by Grauert's theorem, all higher direct images  $R^i \\pi_{2*}(\\pi_1^* \\mathcal{L} \\otimes \\mathcal{O}_{Z_2})$  vanish for  $i \\geq 1$ . Let  $T_X$  be the tangent sheaf of  $X$ .",
